DESCRIPTION:The Al Purdy A-frame Residency offers Canadian writers time and
  space to work at the historic A-frame home built by poet Al Purdy and his
  wife Eurithe on Roblin Lake in Ameliasburgh\, Prince Edward County\, Onta
 rio. Poetry is prioritized\, but all writers are welcome. SUPPORT: CAD 750
  per week stipend and paid return travel (subject to the Association's fun
 draising and Canada Council matching)\; residencies run 3 to 12 weeks. ELI
 GIBILITY: Canadian citizens or permanent residents only. DEADLINE: 18 Sept
 ember 2026 (postmark\, or 4:00pm PT for electronic submissions). Apply via
  the residency page.\n\nOrganisation: The Al Purdy A-frame Association\nLo
 cation: Ameliasburgh\, Prince Edward County\, Ontario\, Canada. Canadian c
 itizens or permanent residents only.\nAward: CAD 750 per week stipend plus
  paid return travel to Ameliasburgh (funding subject to the Association's 
 fundraising and Canada Council matching). Terms of 3 to 12 weeks. No appli
 cation fee.\nDuration: 3 to 12 weeks\n\nMore: https://www.alpurdy.ca/resid
 ency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
